'''''The Son''''' ({{lang-no|Sønnen}}, 2014) is a [[crime novel]] by Norwegian novelist [[Jo Nesbø]]. It is the second stand-alone crime novel by Nesbø, following ''Headhunters'' (2008).

==Plot==
Sonny Lofthus is serving time for crimes he did not commit. As payment, he receives a steady supply of drugs to satisfy his addiction. His life changes completely when he learns the truth about his father's death.<ref>{{cite news|author=Steph Cha|url=http://www.latimes.com/books/jacketcopy/la-ca-jc-jo-nesbo-20140518-story.html|title=Revenge and corruption play a part in Jo Nesbo's thriller 'The Son'|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=May 16, 2014|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=The Son|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-385-35137-9|publisher=[[Publishers Weekly]]|accessdate=May 31, 2014|archivedate=May 14, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140514090620/http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-385-35137-9|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Richard Klinzman|title=Book Review: 'The Son' by Jo Nesbo|url=http://jacksonville.com/entertainment/literature/2014-05-24/story/book-review-son-jo-nesbo|newspaper=[[The Florida Times-Union]]|date=May 24, 2014|accessdate=May 31, 2014|archivedate=May 31, 2014|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140531193528/http://jacksonville.com/entertainment/literature/2014-05-24/story/book-review-son-jo-nesbo|df=}}</ref>

==Inspiration==
Nesbø started work on ''The Son'' during [[Good Friday]] in 2012. The plot is inspired by the Bible.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jo Nesbo talks to Simon Mayo|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01x1p81|publisher=[[BBC]]|accessdate=April 25, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140531190522/http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01x1p81|archivedate=May 31, 2014|deadurl=no|df=}}</ref>

==Adaptation==
A feature film based on the novel is set to be directed by [[Denis Villeneuve]] and produced by [[Jake Gyllenhaal]] and Riva Marker's Nine Stories and Michel Litvak's [[Bold Films]], with [[Jo Nesbø]] executive producing it alongside Niclas Salomonsson.<ref name="adaptation">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/jake-gyllenhaal-denis-villeneuve-crime-movie-son-1201783411/|title=Jake Gyllenhaal, Denis Villeneuve to Reunite for Crime Drama ‘The Son’|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=May 26, 2016|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=October 7, 2016}}</ref>

